- 'Cost of curiosity' is a metaphor for cost-per-click (CPC), referring to the price paid for each click on an ad; 
- An 'information-seeking keyword' refers to a keyword with a search intent of 'I' (Information); 
- A 'significant history' implies more than 5 CPC records for the keyword.

- "Current best position" implies the highest ranking position in search results; 
- "Volume" refers to the search volume of the keyword, indicating its popularity; 
- "Google Desktop searches" refer to searches performed on Google using desktop devices.

sql:
SELECT keyword
FROM keywords
WHERE keyword_id = 1;
